# Project Management Task Breakdown

## Version Control Setup
1. Git Repository Configuration
   - Configure branch protection rules for `main` and `develop`
   - Set up pull request templates
   - Configure required reviews
   - Set up CI/CD basics (if needed)

2. Branching Strategy Implementation
   - Document branching strategy:
     ```
     main (protected)
     └── develop (protected)
         ├── feature/user-system/*
         ├── feature/coa/*
         ├── feature/ledger/*
         ├── feature/reports/*
         └── feature/shared/*
     ```
   - Create initial branches
   - Document merge process
   - Create branch naming conventions

3. Git Workflow Documentation
   - Create quick-start guide
   - Document common Git commands
   - Create troubleshooting guide
   - Document PR process

## Project Board Setup
1. GitHub Projects Configuration
   - Create project board
   - Set up automated workflows:
     - PR creation moves to "In Review"
     - PR merge moves to "Done"
     - Issue assignment moves to "In Progress"

2. Task Organization Structure
   ```
   - User System (Logan)
   - Chart of Accounts (Segun)
   - Account Ledger (Paden)
   - Financial Reports (Thurston)
   - Shared Components (Team)
   ```

3. Label System Creation
   - Priority labels (High/Medium/Low)
   - Type labels (Feature/Bug/Documentation)
   - Status labels (Blocked/Needs Review/Ready)
   - Component labels (User/COA/Ledger/Reports)

## Team Workflow Setup
1. Daily Process Documentation
   - Morning standup format (10 min max):
     - Yesterday's progress
     - Today's goals
     - Blockers
   - End-of-day review format
   - Communication channels
   - Help request process

2. Task Assignment System
   - Create assignment workflow
   - Document task lifecycle
   - Set up notification preferences
   - Create progress tracking system

3. Progress Tracking
   - Create daily checklist template
   - Set up milestone tracking
   - Define completion criteria
   - Create blocker resolution process

## Team Documentation Hub
1. Setup Knowledge Base
   - Create central documentation repository
   - Organize by system component
   - Include getting started guides
   - Add troubleshooting section

2. Component Documentation
   - Create structure for each area:
     ```
     Component/
     ├── Overview.md
     ├── Getting-Started.md
     ├── Architecture.md
     ├── Workflows.md
     └── FAQ.md
     ```
   - Add technical documentation
   - Include workflow guides
   - Add code examples

3. Team Member Guides
   - Create individual task lists
   - Document area responsibilities
   - Add resource links
   - Include contact information

## Quick-Start Documentation
1. Environment Setup Guide
   - Development environment setup
   - Required dependencies
   - Configuration steps
   - Verification process

2. System Overview Guide
   - Architecture overview
   - Component interactions
   - Key workflows
   - Common patterns

3. Workflow Guides
   - Task assignment process
   - Code review process
   - Testing requirements
   - Documentation requirements

## Monitoring and Support
1. Progress Tracking System
   - Create daily progress template
   - Set up milestone tracking
   - Define reporting process
   - Create status dashboard

2. Support System
   - Define escalation process
   - Create help request workflow
   - Document common issues
   - Set up pair programming process

3. Quality Control
   - Define PR review checklist
   - Create testing requirements
   - Document acceptance criteria
   - Set up code quality checks

